theorem
(for G being  strict  finite Group holds (for a being (Element of G) holds ((G = ( gr { a } ) & ( card G ) = n) implies (G = ( gr { ( a |^ k ) } ) iff ( k gcd n ) = 1))))
proof
let G being  strict  finite Group;
let a being (Element of G);
assume that
A1: G = ( gr { a } )
and
A2: ( card G ) = n;
A4: (G = ( gr { ( a |^ k ) } ) implies ( k gcd n ) = 1)
proof
set d = ( k gcd n );
assume that
A5: G = ( gr { ( a |^ k ) } )
and
A6: ( k gcd n ) <> 1;
d divides n by NAT_D:def 5;
then consider p being Nat such that A7: n = ( d * p ) by NAT_D:def 3;
A8: p <> ( 0 ) by A2,A7;
A9: p <> n
proof
assume p = n;
then ( d * p ) = ( p * 1 ) by A7;
hence contradiction by A6,A2,A7,XCMPLX_1:5;
end;
d divides k by NAT_D:def 5;
then consider l being Nat such that A10: k = ( d * l ) by NAT_D:def 3;
A11: (not ( a |^ k ) is  being_of_order_0) by GR_CY_1:6;
( ( a |^ k ) |^ p ) = ( a |^ ( ( l * d ) * p ) ) by A10,GROUP_1:35
.= ( a |^ ( n * l ) ) by A7
.= ( ( a |^ n ) |^ l ) by GROUP_1:35
.= ( ( 1_ G ) |^ l ) by A2,GR_CY_1:9
.= ( 1_ G ) by GROUP_1:31;
then A12: ( ord ( a |^ k ) ) <= p by A8,A11,GROUP_1:def 11;
p divides n by A7,NAT_D:def 3;
then p <= n by A2,NAT_D:7;
then p < n by A9,XXREAL_0:1;
hence contradiction by A2,A5,A12,GR_CY_1:7;
end;
(( k gcd n ) = 1 implies G = ( gr { ( a |^ k ) } ))
proof
assume ( k gcd n ) = 1;
then consider i,i1 such that A13: ( ( i * k ) + ( i1 * n ) ) = 1 by A2,NEWTON:67;
(for b being (Element of G) holds b in ( gr { ( a |^ k ) } ))
proof
let b being (Element of G);
b in G by STRUCT_0:def 5;
then consider i0 such that A14: b = ( a |^ i0 ) by A1,GR_CY_1:5;
A15: i0 = ( ( ( k * i ) + ( n * i1 ) ) * i0 ) by A13
.= ( ( ( k * i ) * i0 ) + ( ( n * i1 ) * i0 ) );
(ex i2 st b = ( ( a |^ k ) |^ i2 ))
proof
take ( i * i0 );
b = ( ( a |^ ( ( k * i ) * i0 ) ) * ( a |^ ( n * ( i1 * i0 ) ) ) ) by A14,A15,GROUP_1:33
.= ( ( a |^ ( ( k * i ) * i0 ) ) * ( ( a |^ n ) |^ ( i1 * i0 ) ) ) by GROUP_1:35
.= ( ( a |^ ( ( k * i ) * i0 ) ) * ( ( 1_ G ) |^ ( i1 * i0 ) ) ) by A2,GR_CY_1:9
.= ( ( a |^ ( ( k * i ) * i0 ) ) * ( 1_ G ) ) by GROUP_1:31
.= ( a |^ ( k * ( i * i0 ) ) ) by GROUP_1:def 4
.= ( ( a |^ k ) |^ ( i * i0 ) ) by GROUP_1:35;
hence thesis;
end;
hence thesis by GR_CY_1:5;
end;
hence thesis by GROUP_2:62;
end;
hence thesis by A4;
end;
